Package jp.go.aist.six.oval.model.linux

Defines a Java object model for the OVAL Linux components.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DpkgInfoItem
    The dpkginfo item stores DPKG package info.
    DpkgInfoObject
    The dpkginfo object is used by a dpkginfo test to define the object to be evaluated.
    DpkgInfoState
    The dpkginfo state defines the different information that can be used to evaluate the specified DPKG package.
    DpkgInfoTest
    The dpkginfo test is used to check information for a given DPKG package.
    EntityItemProtocolType
    The EntityStateProtocolType complex type restricts a string value to the set of physical layer protocols used by AF_PACKET sockets.
    EntityItemRpmVerifyResultType
    The EntityItemRpmVerifyResultType restricts a string value to the set of possible outcomes of checking an attribute of a file included in an RPM against the actual value of that attribute in the RPM database.
    EntityStateProtocolType
    The EntityStateProtocolType restricts a string value to the set of physical layer protocols used by AF_PACKET sockets.
    EntityStateRpmVerifyResultType
    The EntityStateRpmVerifyResultType restricts a string value to the set of possible outcomes of checking an attribute of a file included in an RPM against the actual value of that attribute in the RPM database.
    FileBehaviors
    The FileBehaviors defines a number of behaviors that allow a more detailed definition of a set of files or file related items to collect.
    IfListenersItem
    An iflisteners_item stores the results of checking for applications that are bound to an interface on the system.
    IfListenersObject
    The iflisteners_object element is used by an iflisteners_test to define the specific interface to be evaluated.
    IfListenersState
    The iflisteners_state element defines the different information that can be used to evaluate the specified applications that are listening on interfaces on the system.
    IfListenersTest
    The iflisteners_test is used to check what applications such as packet sniffers that are bound to an interface on the system.
    InetListeningServersItem
    An inet listening server item stores the results of checking for network servers currently active on a system.
    InetListeningServersObject
    The inetlisteningservers object is used by an inet listening servers test to define the specific protocol-address-port to be evaluated.
    InetListeningServersState
    The inetlisteningservers state defines the different information that can be used to evaluate the specified inet listening server.
    InetListeningServersTest
    The inet listening servers test is used to check what applications are listening on the network.

    LinuxEvrPkgInfoState  
    LinuxPkg  
    LinuxPkgInfoItem  
    LinuxPkgInfoObject

    PartitionItem
    The partition item stores information about a partition on the local system.
    PartitionObject
    The partition object is used by a partition test to define which partitions on the local system should be collected.
    PartitionState
    The partition state defines the different information associated with a partition.
    PartitionTest
    The partition test is used to check the information associated with partitions on the local system.
    RpmInfoBehaviors
    The RpmInfoBehaviors defines a set of behaviors for controlling what data, for installed rpms, is collected.
    RpmInfoItem
    The rpminfo item stores rpm info.
    RpmInfoObject
    The rpminfo object is used by a rpminfo test to define the object to be evaluated.
    RpmInfoState
    The rpminfo state defines the different information that can be used to evaluate the specified rpm.
    RpmInfoTest
    The rpminfo test is used to check the RPM header information for a given RPM package.
    RpmVerifyBehaviors Deprecated
    Deprecated as of version 5.10: Replaced by the RpmVerifyFileBehaviors and the RpmVerifyPackageBehaviors and will be removed in version 6.0 of the language.
    RpmVerifyFileBehaviors
    The RpmVerifyFileBehaviors defines a set of behaviors that for controlling how the individual files in installed rpms are verified.
    RpmVerifyFileItem
    This item stores the verification results of the individual files in an RPM similar to what is produced by the rpm -V command.
    RpmVerifyFileObject
    The rpmverifyfile_object is used by a rpmverifyfile_test to define a set of files within a set of RPMs to verify.
    RpmVerifyFileState
    The rpmverifyfile_state defines the different information that can be used to determine if a set of files within a set of RPMs passed verification.
    RpmVerifyFileTest
    The rpmverifyfile_test is used to verify the integrity of the individual files in installed RPMs.
    RpmVerifyItem Deprecated
    Deprecated as of version 5.10: Replaced by the rpmverifyfile item and rpmverifypackage item and will be removed in version 6.0 of the language.
    RpmVerifyObject Deprecated
    Deprecated as of version 5.10: Replaced by the rpmverifyfile object and rpmverifypackage object and will be removed in version 6.0 of the language.
    RpmVerifyPackageBehaviors
    The RpmVerifyPackageBehaviors complex type defines a set of behaviors that for controlling how installed rpms are verified.
    RpmVerifyPackageItem
    This item stores the rpm verification results of an rpm similar to what is produced by the rpm -V command.
    RpmVerifyPackageObject
    The rpmverifypackage_object is used by a rpmverity_test to define a set of RPMs to verify.
    RpmVerifyPackageState
    The rpmverifypackage_state defines the different information that can be used to verify the integrity of installed RPMs.
    RpmVerifyPackageTest
    The rpmverifypackage_test is used to verify the integrity of installed RPMs.
    RpmVerifyState Deprecated
    Deprecated as of version 5.10: Replaced by the rpmverifyfile state and rpmverifypackage state and will be removed in version 6.0 of the language.
    RpmVerifyTest Deprecated
    Deprecated as of version 5.10: Replaced by the rpmverifyfile test and rpmverifyfile test and will be removed in version 6.0 of the language.
    SelinuxBooleanItem
    This item describes the current and pending status of a SELinux boolean.
    SelinuxBooleanObject
    The selinuxboolean object is used by an selinuxboolean test to define the items to evaluate based on a specified state.
    SelinuxBooleanState
    The selinuxboolean state defines the different information that can be used to evaluate the specified SELinux boolean.
    SelinuxBooleanTest
    The selinuxboolean test is used to check the current and pending status of a SELinux boolean.
    SelinuxSecurityContextItem
    This item describes the SELinux security context of a file or process on the local system.
    SelinuxSecurityContextObject
    The selinuxsecuritycontext object is used by an selinuxsecuritycontext test to define the security contexts of files and processes to collect from the local system.
    SelinuxSecurityContextState
    The selinuxsecuritycontext state defines the different information that can be used to evaluate the specified SELinux security context.
    SelinuxSecurityContextTest
    The selinuxsecuritycontext test is used to check the security context of a file or process on the local system.
    SlackwarePkgInfoItem
    This item describes info related to Slackware packages.
    SlackwarePkgInfoObject
    The slackwarepkginfo object is used by a slackware package info test to define the object to be evaluated.
    SlackwarePkgInfoState
    The slackwarepkginfo state defines the different information that can be used to evaluate the specified package.
    SlackwarePkgInfoTest
    The slackware package info test is used to check information associated with a given Slackware package.
